  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/08e1c4a93c17eac9c62220f0ee243d0d08ab4507" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:62.986ex; height:7.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle G_{Y}(z)=\sum \limits _{n=0}^{\infty }P(Y=n)z^{n}=\exp \left(\sum _{k=1}^{\infty }\alpha _{k}\lambda (z^{k}-1)\right),\quad (|z|\leq 1)}"/></span></dd></dl>
<p>has a discrete pseudo <a href="/wiki/Compound_Poisson_distribution" title="Compound Poisson distribution">compound Poisson distribution</a> with parameters
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle (\lambda _{1},\lambda _{2},\ldots )=(\alpha _{1}\lambda ,\alpha _{2}\lambda ,\ldots )\in \mathbb {R} ^{\infty }\left(\sum _{k=1}^{\infty }\alpha _{k}=1,\sum \limits _{k=1}^{\infty }|\alpha _{k}|&lt;\infty ,\alpha _{k}\in \mathbb {R} ,\lambda &gt;0\right).}">
